<TITLE> NATO plane crashes after takeoff in Afghanistan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KABUL, May 14 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A single-seat NATO aircraft crashed after takeoff in southern Afghanistan on Thursday, injuring the pilot, the alliance said. A spokesman for the alliance, which leads a military force in the country, said cause of the crash was mechanical failure. The pilot ejected and was taken to a medical facility. There were no other casualties, he said. He was unable to give details of the type of airplane involved, the nationality of the pilot or the location within southern Afghanistan.
